                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Republic of Korea’s Delegate to the armistice talks at Panmunjom, Major
                    General <persName corresp="#p_CDS1">Choi Duk Shin</persName>, who had been
                    boycotting the plenary sessions since May 15, 1953, was recalled by his
                    government on June 7, 1953. <persName corresp="#p_CDS1">Choi</persName> and his
                    entire staff left Munsan-ni; no Koreans remained in the United Nations Command
                    base camp. (Telegram C 62874, <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> to
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>, June 7, 1953; <persName
                        corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D 413)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
